            {
              "code": "M1",
              "type": "M",
              "value": 1,
              "criterion": "Multiplies out and attempts to differentiate. Award for one correct index from correct working (may be implied if they multiply out and differentiate at the same time) $t^{\\frac{3}{2}}$, $t^{\\frac{1}{2}}$ or $t^{-\\frac{1}{2}}$ (condone if these are $\\alpha^{\\frac{3}{2}}$, $\\alpha^{\\frac{1}{2}}$ or $\\alpha^{-\\frac{1}{2}}$ or any other variable). The indices do not need to be processed for this mark. e.g. $5t^{\\frac{1}{2}}$. Alternatively, they may attempt the product rule so look for a correct general expression such as $\\frac{\\text{d}H}{\\text{d}t} = ... (20t + 6t^{\\frac{1}{2}}) + ... (t^{\\frac{1}{2}} + At^{-\\frac{1}{2}} + Bt^{-\\frac{3}{2}})$ (condone if in terms of $\\alpha$ or another variable instead)"
            },
            {
              "code": "A1",
              "type": "A",
              "value": 1,
              "criterion": "One of $\\frac{1}{2} t^{\\frac{1}{2}}$, $\\frac{9}{2} t^{-\\frac{1}{2}}$, $-\\frac{1}{8} t^{-\\frac{3}{2}}$ (simplified or unsimplified) via the main scheme. If they differentiate using the product rule then this mark can only be awarded for one of $\\frac{1}{2} t^{-\\frac{1}{2}} (20t + 6t^{\\frac{1}{2}}) + ...$ or $... + (t^{\\frac{1}{2}} + \\frac{1}{2} t^{-\\frac{1}{2}} + \\frac{1}{2} t^{-\\frac{3}{2}}) (6t - 2t^{-\\frac{1}{2}})$ (unsimplified). In both cases the indices must be processed. Condone if in terms of $\\alpha$"
            },
            {
              "code": "A1",
              "type": "A",
              "value": 1,
              "criterion": "$\\frac{\\text{d}H}{\\text{d}t} = \\frac{1}{2} t^{\\frac{1}{2}} + \\frac{9}{2} t^{-\\frac{1}{2}} - \\frac{1}{8} t^{-\\frac{3}{2}}$ or equivalent e.g. $\\frac{\\text{d}H}{\\text{d}t} = \\frac{1}{40} t^{-\\frac{3}{2}} (20t^2 + 18t - 5)$ which may be unsimplified. Also allow e.g. $\\frac{\\text{d}H}{\\text{d}t} = \\frac{1}{2} t^{-\\frac{1}{2}} (20t + 6t^{\\frac{1}{2}}) + (t^{\\frac{1}{2}} + \\frac{1}{2} t^{-\\frac{1}{2}} + \\frac{1}{2} t^{-\\frac{3}{2}}) (6t - 2t^{-\\frac{1}{2}})$ (via the product rule)"
            },
            {
              "code": "dM1",
              "type": "M",
              "value": 1,
              "criterion": "Sets their derivative of the form $... t^{\\frac{3}{2}} \\pm ... t^{\\frac{1}{2}} \\pm ... t^{-\\frac{1}{2}} = 0$ (may be implied) and proceeds via a correct method to a 3TQ in $t$ or $\\alpha$ (or any other variable) where the powers and the coefficients of the terms are integers. Condone sign slips only. It is dependent on the previous method mark. Proceeding directly to the given answer is M0, unless they state how they have proceeded from the derivative directly to the given answer e.g. set $t = \\alpha$ and $\\times 40t^{\\frac{3}{2}}$. Derivatives which are already factorised before being set $= 0$ and have the quadratic factor $20t^2 + 18t - 5$ can score this mark for e.g. $\\frac{1}{40} t^{-\\frac{3}{2}} (20t^2 + 18t - 5) = 0 \\Rightarrow 5t^2 - 18t - 20 = 0$"
            },
            {
              "code": "A1*",
